On Escalation Ticket # 00436501 the new comment has been added: Customer uses an API which calls dropbox.com. The policy blocks the API call from completing and generates an error message. I have uploaded the message to Attachments on this ticket. Customer needs to allow www.dropbox.com while blocking www.dropbox.com/login. Is it possible to allow dropbox.com and block www.dropbox.com/login?  Thank you for your assistance.

On Escalation Ticket # 00436501 the new comment has been added: Is it possible to allow www.dropbox.com and block www.dropbox.com/login? Customer is encountering issues with using API calls relating to www.dropbox.com and would like to know if keeping the policy active while also using the API calls can be possible. Thank you.
